main event: A civilian reported observing a bright solid object in the sky near Hilbert, Wisconsin on 14 March 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as brighter than the brightest star and compared to a red hot iron., The object had an apparent size similar to the moon., It made a humming noise during observation., The object was in sight for approximately 15 minutes., Another eyewitness reported seeing two bluish-white beams of light from their house.
